.TH VENV "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
venv \- Setup a Python virtual environment
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B venv
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,DIRECTORY\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B venv
is a script for setting up Python virtual environments. It simplifies the creation and management of isolated Python environments for project development.
.PP
The script handles virtual environment creation and activation setup.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B venv myproject
Create virtual environment in myproject directory
.TP
.B venv .venv
Create virtual environment in .venv directory
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/venv/settings.conf
User configuration file for venv preferences
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Creates isolated Python environments
.IP \(bu 2
Supports different Python versions
.IP \(bu 2
Simplifies environment activation
